canonical:
  title: 賀麟見表
  author: 無名氏
  language: lzh
  text: 一人御極光啓昌期二儀儲祥茂昭景貺照臨所曁歡抃惟均竊觀仁獸之生實爲王者之瑞在黃帝而遊於囿逮蒼姬而見于郊誠曠世之罕聞幸明時之復覩欽惟心敦位育道合彌綸運撫盈成神化覃於八表恩孚動植和氣塞于兩閒顧玆靈物之臻允協禎符之應伏念猥以庸質獲際煕朝迹滯鯷岑雖阻駿奔之列情馳鳳闕倍殫虎拜之誠
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀麟見表
  author: 無名氏
  language: lzh
  text: 一人御極。光啓昌期。二儀儲祥。茂昭景貺。照臨所曁。歡抃惟均。竊觀仁獸之生。實爲王者之瑞。在黃帝而遊於囿。逮蒼姬而見于郊。誠曠世之罕聞。幸明時之復覩。欽惟心敦位育。道合彌綸。運撫盈成。神化覃於八表。恩孚動植。和氣塞于兩閒。顧玆靈物之臻。允協禎符之應。伏念猥以庸質。獲際煕朝。迹滯鯷岑。雖阻駿奔之列。情馳鳳闕。倍殫虎拜之誠。
korean:
  title: 기린이 나타난 것을 하례하는 표
  author: 무명씨
  language: kor
  text: 한 분이 지존(至尊)에 임어하시어 성대(盛代)를 환하게 여시고, 이의(二儀 하늘과 땅)가 상서를 모아 아름다운 선물을 풍성히 나타내시니, 해와 달이 비치는 곳에 기뻐 춤춤이 오직 고르도소이다.그윽히 보건대, 이 어진 짐승이 난 것은 실로 왕자(王者)의 상서이니, 황제(黃帝) 때에는 동산[囿]에 나와 노닐었고, 창희(蒼姬 주나라)에 미쳐서는 들밖에 나타났는데, 진실로 광세(曠世)의 희한한 일이거늘 다행히 이 명시(明時)에 다시금 보게 되었나이다.공경히 생각건대, 황제폐하께서 마음은 만물의 화육(化育)에 돈독하고 정도(正道)는 천지의 경륜에 합하시어 천운(天運)으로 영성(盈成)을 어루만지시니 신화(神化)가 팔표(八表 팔방)에 두루 미치고, 은혜가 동식(動植)에 흡족하며 화기(和氣)가 천지간에 가득하니, 이번에 이 영물이 나타남은 실로 상서로운 징표(徵表)가 응함이로소이다.엎드려 생각건대, 외람되이 용렬한 자질로써 희조(熙朝)를 만나 몸이 제잠(鯷岑)에 걸려있으므로 비록 준분(駿奔)의 반열에 참가하지는 못하오나, 정은 봉궐(鳳闕)에 달려 갑절이나 호배(虎拜)의 정성을 다하나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0360_010_0100&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Memorial Celebrating the Appearance of the Qilin
  language: eng
  text: |-
    One sovereign ascends to the highest seat, illuminating an age of prosperity. Heaven and Earth gather their blessings, abundantly displaying their gracious gifts. Wherever the light of sun and moon reaches, joy dances in perfect harmony.

    Observing with reverence, this benevolent beast's appearance is truly an auspicious sign of virtuous rule. In the time of the Yellow Emperor it roamed the imperial park, and in the age of the Zhou it appeared in the distant fields—a marvel rarely witnessed across the ages. Yet in this enlightened era, fortune grants us to see it once more.

    With utmost respect, I contemplate how Your Majesty's heart is devoted to nurturing all life, your righteous way aligned with heaven's governance. Through the working of destiny you perfect all things, and divine transformation spreads across the eight directions. Your grace extends to all creatures, and harmonious energy fills the space between heaven and earth. That this spiritual being now appears is surely heaven's response, confirming the auspicious omens.

    Humbly I reflect that I, a person of humble talents, have been blessed to witness this glorious age. Though my station confines me far from the ranks of the swift and noble, my heart races toward your palace, and I offer the sincerest reverence of this insignificant subject.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The qilin (麟) is a legendary hooved chimera representing benevolent rule and imperial virtue in Chinese tradition.
  - key: ''
    value: The Yellow Emperor and Zhou dynasty are references to ancient sage-kings, eras when qilins were said to have appeared as signs of virtuous governance.
  - key: ''
    value: This memorial follows the classical Chinese commemorative form, celebrating the appearance of the auspicious creature as validation of the current ruler's virtue.
